                    Radio Frequency Management Objectives
    Richard Barth is Chief of the Radio Frequency Management Division and
   Director of the Office of Radio Frequency Management. He can be reached
     by phone at 301-713-1853 or by FAX at 301-713-1861, and by EMAIL at
                           richard.barth@noaa.gov.
                              Major Activities:
     * Provides policy guidance and technical and procedural support for
       all elements of the Department of Commerce in the assignment,
       management and use of radio frequencies.
     * Represents the Department of Commerce nationally and
       internationally in matters relating to the allocation and
       regulation of radio frequencies.
     * With the agreement of the Department of State, represents the
       United States at international conferences on matters relating to
       the allocation and use of the radio spectrum.
     * Responsible for obtaining, assigning and protecting from harmful
       interference radio frequencies used by all elements of the
       Department of Commerce.

